Seizes 10.89kg cocaine at Lagos airport, 2.3million tramadol tabs, bottles of codeine in Kaduna
Operatives of the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) have intercepted travellers cheques in different foreign currencies with a total value of N1.1b at the Murtala Muhammed International Airport (MMIA), Ikeja. Lagos.
    
The operatives also arrested a suspect, Oguma Richard Uchenna , in connection to attempt to export the cheques, which were neatly concealed inside four bound hard cover books disguised as academic project literatures, to the United Kingdom (UK).
   
Spokesperson for the agency, Femi Babafemi, in a statement yesterday, said the financial instruments suspected to be counterfeits were discovered on Wednesday, April 27, at Nigerian Aviation Handling Company Plc (NAHCO) export shed of the Lagos airport, during cargo examination of some consignments meant for exportation to the UK on a cargo flight.  MEANWHILE, Chairman/Chief Executive of NDLEA, Brig. Gen. Mohammed Buba Marwa (Retd), has commended officers and men of the MMIA, Ondo, Akwa Ibom and Kaduna Commands of the agency for the seizures and arrests in the past week.
     
He charged them and their compatriots across the country to remain steadfast and vigilant in their areas of responsibility. 